### Example 1: Get JSON of all Displays
GET http://localhost:8080/display/all

### Example 2: Adding a Display to the Database
POST http://localhost:8080/display/add
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

macAddress=00:00:00:00:02 &
brand=Phillips &
model=Tableux &
width=1920 &
height=1080 &
orientation=vertical &
filename=flora.jpg

### Example 3: Deleting a Display by MAC
DELETE http://localhost:8080/display/delete/00:00:00:00:99

### Example 4: Download an image from the server
GET http://localhost:8080/image/download/moon.jpg

### Example 5: Initiate a Display with it's mac address
POST http://localhost:8080/display/initiate
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

macAddress=00:00:00:00:02 &
width=1920 &
height=1080

### Example 6: Get single Display based on MAC
GET http://localhost:8080/display/get/00:00:00:00:01

### Example 7: Delete image based on Filename
DELETE http://localhost:8080/image/delete/test_delete_image.jpg

### Example 8: Get all Events
GET http://localhost:8080/event/all

### Example 9: Get all Events for a specific Display
GET http://localhost:8080/event/all/00:00:00:00:02

### Example 10: Add a new Event
POST http://localhost:8080/event/add
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

title=Meeting &
allDay=false &
start=2024-12-12T07:00:00 &
end=2024-12-12T08:00:00 &
displayMac=00:00:00:00:02 &
image=moon.jpg

### Example 11: Update an Event
PUT http://localhost:8080/event/update/1
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

title=Updated Meeting &
allDay=false &
start=2024-12-12T10:30:00 &
end=2024-12-12T11:30:00 &
image=flora.jpg

### Example 12: Delete an Event by ID
DELETE http://localhost:8080/event/delete/1